# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Return Genie — root environment pointer
#
# There is NO single root .env. Each deployable reads its own .env. Copy the
# per-app example below and fill it in. Full reference: docs/ENVIRONMENT.md
#
#   apps/backend/.env.example   → apps/backend/.env          (backend API + processing)
#   apps/admin/.env.example     → apps/admin/.env.local      (admin SPA, VITE_* only)
#   apps/desktop/.env.example   → apps/desktop/.env          (desktop main process)
#
# Quick start:
#   cp apps/backend/.env.example apps/backend/.env
#   cp apps/admin/.env.example   apps/admin/.env.local
#   cp apps/desktop/.env.example apps/desktop/.env
#
# Secrets (DB URLs, Supabase service-role key, EXTERNAL_API_* creds) live ONLY in
# the backend env / host dashboard — never in the admin or desktop client.
# CI/CD secrets live in GitHub Actions secrets — see docs/DEPLOYMENT.md §5.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
